  <input>What is a Hadamard Gate?</input>
  <output>A Hadamard Gate is a fundamental quantum logic gate that transforms a qubit into a superposition of states. It takes the basis states |0⟩ and |1⟩ and maps them to equal superpositions: |0⟩ becomes (|0⟩ + |1⟩)/√2, and |1⟩ becomes (|0⟩ - |1⟩)/√2. This gate is crucial in quantum computing for creating superposition, enabling quantum parallelism and interference effects that are essential for quantum algorithms.</output>
  </example>
  <example>
  <input>What are the basis states of the Hadamard Gate?</input>
  <output>|0> = [1 0] and |1> = [0 1]</output>
  </example>
